---
title: Chickpea-Powered Mediterranean Bulgur with Zucchini & Grape Tomatoes
description: You haven’t tasted chickpeas until you’ve tried them roasted. Deliciously crunchy and more than worth the time they spend in a hot oven. In this recipe, they’re roasted with smoked paprika and tossed with toasted bulgur, roasted zucchini and tomatoes, and feta cheese for a mishmash of savory Mediterranean flavors. You likely won’t have leftovers, but if you do, you’ll find the dish tastes even better the next day.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/633334461ef63afce30f0c8f-b58a6f30.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/chickpea-powered-mediterranean-bulgur-633334461ef63afce30f0c8f-4700341a.pdf
time required: 30 minutes
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/chickpea-powered-mediterranean-bulgur-633334461ef63afce30f0c8f
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: Mediterranean
nutrition:
  calories: 560 kcal
  fat: 23 g
  saturated fat: 10 g
  carbohydrates: 73 g
  sugar: 12 g
  protein: 18 g
  fiber: 14 g
  sodium: 820 mg
course: main course
---

Adjust racks to middle and top positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and dice @zucchini{1} into ½-inch pieces. Halve @grape tomatoes{4%oz}. Strip @thyme{1/4%oz} leaves from stems. Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Halve @lemon{1}.

Toss zucchini, tomatoes, and half the thyme leaves on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on middle rack, tossing halfway through, until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse @chickpeas{1%unit}; dry thoroughly with #paper towels{}. On a second baking sheet, toss half the chickpeas (all for 4 servings) with a large drizzle of olive oil, @smoked paprika{1%tsp}, and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Roast on top rack, tossing halfway through, until crisp, ~{18-20%minutes}.

> It's natural for chickpeas to pop a bit while roasting.

While chickpeas roast, heat @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings), garlic, and scallion whites in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat; cook until butter melts and garlic is fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add @bulgur wheat{1/2%cup} and remaining thyme leaves; stir to coat. Season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until bulgur is lightly toasted, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add @veggie stock concentrate{1} and @water{1%cup} (2 cups for 4 servings) to pot with bulgur. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until bulgur is tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Add half the veggies, half the @feta cheese{1/2%cup}, and a squeeze of lemon juice to pot with bulgur; stir to combine. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide between plates or shallow bowls; top with chickpeas and remaining veggies. Garnish with scallion greens and remaining feta. Serve.